race.comment: DE GRANDHOMME (1) was only 0.8L off the winner last start at Northam and should appreciate the rise up to 1200m today. Needs some luck from the outside barrier, but he's nicely weighted after the claim of Cheung. Keeps hinting that he's better than this grade, he just needs to put it all together now. SWANSEE (5) drops back to 1200m today after feeling the pinch late over 1400m in her past couple of outings. Should be at her peak fitness now though and the early speed she possesses is a big positive. Can be right in the finish. YALLINGUP GIRL (8) only just missed over this track and trip last start when sitting just off the speed. Galati replaces the apprentice hoop now and he maps for a similar run third-up into the campaign. Up in weight but can land the knockout blow. UNDERCOVER SNIPER (3) is building nicely this time in and has to be included third-up. LIVE LUCKY (7) missed as favourite first-up but will be better for that run. Worth including.
